
Core9-platform now needs at least a 2.6 mongodb version.


chmod 755 gradlew
./gradlew --refresh-dependencies install
cd build/install/core9-platform-master-stable
./bin/core9-platform-master


For windows use Cygwin to run the commands.

http://www.cygwin.com/install.html


If you have unresolved dependencies go to this page : https://bintray.com/core9/core9

and change the + in the build.gradle with the latest version number of the module that is causing problems.